00:40:29.130 --> 00:40:34.210
Annie: That is an excellent question.

00:40:34.210 --> 00:40:38.500
Okay, so how do you assess emotional intelligence
in an interview for example.

00:40:38.500 --> 00:40:41.569
It's easy to assess technical capabilities
usually.

00:40:41.569 --> 00:40:44.181
It's difficult to assess emotional intelligence.

00:40:44.181 --> 00:40:46.971
All right, there are a couple of things that
you can do.

00:40:46.971 --> 00:40:52.109
First of all, you've got to turn on your "empathy"
 , okay, and be really watchful about the

00:40:52.109 --> 00:40:53.490
person's behavior.

00:40:53.490 --> 00:40:59.549
And the kinds of things you're looking for
are curiosity about you, curiosity about the

00:40:59.549 --> 00:41:04.460
situation; are they open to looking at the
situation and making sense of it?

00:41:04.460 --> 00:41:07.119
Okay, that would be sort of reaching out and
looking.

00:41:07.119 --> 00:41:09.740
Are they able to express empathy in the form
of curiosity?

00:41:09.740 --> 00:41:13.579
Are they able to express social awareness
by how they showed up and what they're wearing,

00:41:13.579 --> 00:41:14.579
and all of the rest of that.

00:41:14.579 --> 00:41:17.390
So you can use your own powers of observation.

00:41:17.390 --> 00:41:22.460
My favorite way to try to get at the heart
of that without a formal assessment is to

00:41:22.460 --> 00:41:28.859
ask them to tell me a story, a real story,
about a situation in which they were expected

00:41:28.859 --> 00:41:32.529
to lead, and the group was very difficult,
and what they did.

00:41:32.529 --> 00:41:37.369
And then, as I'm listening, I'm coding for
the competencies. I'm coding for emotional

00:41:37.369 --> 00:41:39.599
self-awareness.
Did they fly off the handle?

00:41:39.599 --> 00:41:41.430
I'm coding for self-management.

00:41:41.430 --> 00:41:46.380
I'm coding for the initiative. I'm coding
for the ability to even look at difficult

00:41:46.380 --> 00:41:48.519
situations positively.

00:41:48.519 --> 00:41:53.619
So, those are some tips, but I want to answer
the question in one other way, okay?

00:41:53.619 --> 00:41:59.900
Formal assessment, in my belief, in my sort
of research background, it's impossible for

00:41:59.900 --> 00:42:03.890
individuals to self assess their own emotional
intelligence.

00:42:03.890 --> 00:42:05.490
Why is that?

00:42:05.490 --> 00:42:11.039
If you're not self aware, how can you possible
measure your emotional intelligence?

00:42:11.039 --> 00:42:17.280
So, we use group level evaluation when we're
trying to assess emotional intelligence.

00:42:17.280 --> 00:42:20.849
Really, it's other people's opinions, but
if you get enough, you've got a hint about

00:42:20.849 --> 00:42:21.849
where you're going.

00:42:21.849 --> 00:42:27.261
So if you have the opportunity to do the 360,
or to get data, that's using emotional intelligence

00:42:27.261 --> 00:42:30.150
competencies, you're more likely to be able
to see that profile.

00:42:30.150 --> 00:42:36.150
But short of that, using what we call a critical
event interview, having them tell you about

00:42:36.150 --> 00:42:38.779
an event and literally coding yourself helps.

00:42:38.779 --> 00:42:42.289
Or you can ask them to write it down ahead
of time, before they come in.

00:42:42.289 --> 00:42:45.119
And literally, sort of qualitative research,
code it.

