00:43:35.770 --> 00:43:39.369
And that's absolutely true, absolutely true.

00:43:39.369 --> 00:43:40.809
There's two answers to this, okay.

00:43:40.809 --> 00:43:42.380
The first one is more macro.

00:43:42.380 --> 00:43:43.839
How do people learn?

00:43:43.839 --> 00:43:48.500
Okay, so the first step in the learning process
is to make sure that you actually care about

00:43:48.500 --> 00:43:49.970
learning, and you want to.

00:43:49.970 --> 00:43:51.339
That's the first step.

00:43:51.339 --> 00:43:53.390
You've got to attach it to something bigger.

00:43:53.390 --> 00:43:54.710
I'll give you a quick example.

00:43:54.710 --> 00:43:57.410
There's this one executive I was working with
in Italy.

00:43:57.410 --> 00:44:01.730
Actually. I was coaching him, and he had a
problem with empathy.

00:44:01.730 --> 00:44:03.490
I mean, he was just tearing his team apart.

00:44:03.490 --> 00:44:08.480
He was the Deputy CEO, slotted to be the CEO,
but he wasn't going to get there unless he

00:44:08.480 --> 00:44:09.480
fixed this problem.

00:44:09.480 --> 00:44:13.690
He'd been told, "You either stop destroying
teams or it's over."

00:44:13.690 --> 00:44:17.210
And he was like, "Empathy? How can I learn
about that? I don't really care about it,

00:44:17.210 --> 00:44:18.210
anyway."

00:44:18.210 --> 00:44:19.210
[laughter]

00:44:19.210 --> 00:44:22.670
Through the coaching process, he didn't, he
really didn't.

00:44:22.670 --> 00:44:27.780
Through the coaching process, not quite sure
how it happened because I did not ask him

00:44:27.780 --> 00:44:28.780
about his family.

00:44:28.780 --> 00:44:30.710
That's sort of the line in coaching.

00:44:30.710 --> 00:44:36.359
It came to him that this lack of empathy,
was actually interfering with his relationship

00:44:36.359 --> 00:44:40.089
with his wife and most importantly his 14-year-old
daughter.

00:44:40.089 --> 00:44:43.520
This light bulb went off in this guy's head,
and he was like, "Okay, I'm getting a handle

00:44:43.520 --> 00:44:45.210
on this thing. I'm going to do it."

00:44:45.210 --> 00:44:49.200
And so we went through some processes, which
will bring me to the second part of the question

00:44:49.200 --> 00:44:53.150
of helping him to see when he needed it, and
how to practice it, okay.

00:44:53.150 --> 00:44:56.869
So, number one you've got to figure why you
want to change this thing.

00:44:56.869 --> 00:44:59.910
Second you're absolutely right.

00:44:59.910 --> 00:45:01.859
It takes practice.

00:45:01.859 --> 00:45:03.750
It doesn't happen overnight.

00:45:03.750 --> 00:45:08.759
You need to become almost like a helicopter
over yourself, viewing your own behavior and

00:45:08.759 --> 00:45:11.369
emotions consciously.

00:45:11.369 --> 00:45:14.630
And checking when you're going off the path,
okay.

00:45:14.630 --> 00:45:19.789
You also need some understanding of how you
can create experiments for yourself and to

00:45:19.789 --> 00:45:23.220
improve slowly over time.

00:45:23.220 --> 00:45:29.450
And note those markers on some sort of mental
map, and usually that doesn't happen easily,

00:45:29.450 --> 00:45:31.329
unless you've got some help.

00:45:31.329 --> 00:45:35.980
You need somebody -- a friend, your partner,
whatever, you need somebody to be in it with

00:45:35.980 --> 00:45:38.269
you giving support, because it's not that
easy.

00:45:38.269 --> 00:45:43.859
And then last but not least, especially when
it comes to mindfulness.

00:45:43.859 --> 00:45:44.950
It's a daily practice.

00:45:44.950 --> 00:45:48.980
Let me give you some very practical ideas,
okay.

00:45:48.980 --> 00:45:54.769
If you're trying to deepen your capacity for
mindfulness, you really think that's probably

00:45:54.769 --> 00:45:58.210
the first place to start, which for most people
I believe it is.

00:45:58.210 --> 00:45:59.640
You can do some really simple things.

00:45:59.640 --> 00:46:05.720
You don't need to meditate 4 hours a day or
take 16 weeks off and go to wherever in meditation

00:46:05.720 --> 00:46:06.720
patient retreat.

00:46:06.720 --> 00:46:07.720
You really don't.

00:46:07.720 --> 00:46:08.789
You really don't need to do yoga every day.

00:46:08.789 --> 00:46:12.440
If you do these things, more power to you.

00:46:12.440 --> 00:46:18.279
What it takes is just a little bit of time,
every single day.

00:46:18.279 --> 00:46:23.259
Where you're not doing the stress routine,
you're are not making the to-do lists, you're

00:46:23.259 --> 00:46:24.880
not worrying about what's happening at home.

00:46:24.880 --> 00:46:29.099
You're not worrying about the project that's
running off the rails or whatever.

00:46:29.099 --> 00:46:30.099
You're quiet.

00:46:30.099 --> 00:46:33.970
I mean, literally 10 minutes in bed before
you get up.

00:46:33.970 --> 00:46:40.529
Emptying your mind, breathing deep, oxygen
affects all this, you all probably know that,

00:46:40.529 --> 00:46:41.529
makes a difference.

00:46:41.529 --> 00:46:47.990
Twenty minutes walking from one building to
another without anybody else, by yourself,

00:46:47.990 --> 00:46:50.650
not fussing about what's happening next.

00:46:50.650 --> 00:46:55.690
It sounds so trivial, but those little things
make a difference.

00:46:55.690 --> 00:47:01.519
And as you become accustomed to this habit,
you can turn it on instantaneously.

00:47:01.519 --> 00:47:05.740
Before I get up and do a talk I will go over
for 5 minutes and sort of, whew, get rid of

00:47:05.740 --> 00:47:13.069
whatever is there, and then I'm back to sort
of a nice, resilient place again.

00:47:13.069 --> 00:47:16.800
I don't want to over simplify this, but if
we try to make it complex, none of us are

00:47:16.800 --> 00:47:19.000
going to do it.

00:47:19.000 --> 00:47:27.390
Get out on your bike, go for a run, go for
a walk, get away from people, focus on clear

00:47:27.390 --> 00:47:29.440
and calm.

00:47:29.440 --> 00:47:30.490
Good question.

00:47:30.490 --> 00:47:31.490
Others?

00:47:31.490 --> 00:47:32.990
Anybody else?

00:47:32.990 --> 00:47:33.990
Yes.

