00:47:41.160 --> 00:47:44.109
How do we interact with the people who aren't
at this talk?

00:47:44.109 --> 00:47:49.059
Who do not have emotional intelligence, or
at least don't use it?

00:47:49.059 --> 00:47:52.880
The first thing I would say is what was on
one of the slides, don't be a victim, and

00:47:52.880 --> 00:47:54.999
just don't go there.

00:47:54.999 --> 00:47:57.849
Secondly, build some good fat walls around
you.

00:47:57.849 --> 00:48:00.940
So they don't hurt you.

00:48:00.940 --> 00:48:01.941
Don't let these people hurt you.

00:48:01.941 --> 00:48:05.630
They're trying to hurt you in some cases,
and in other cases they don't know, but in

00:48:05.630 --> 00:48:10.450
either case don't let them hurt you because
they can really damage your self-esteem.

00:48:10.450 --> 00:48:14.920
Then the third is don't do it back.

00:48:14.920 --> 00:48:21.249
If you do it back, you're just facilitating
the growth of a beast inside your group.

00:48:21.249 --> 00:48:24.829
So don't be a victim, boundaries, and don't
do it back.

00:48:24.829 --> 00:48:26.070
And go do good where you can.

00:48:26.070 --> 00:48:31.609
Fourth, fourth, right the fourth and final
suggestion -- if it's like that chronically,

00:48:31.609 --> 00:48:33.549
